channel.title: Consensus on RS2 Cheating
channel.description:
I've been thinking of updating my few thousand lines of code into a workable bot from the heap of alerts it currently gives... What I'm wondering though, is now that all the pleasure of massive loot from an epic PKER is gone, coincided with the fact that there's absolutely no profitability, is there any reason for us to even continue with the game?
I mean, should we hack a game that no one really plays now that they've taken two or more(pking, dueling, rares) major aspects of the game, making it into an almost pointless endeavor for legitimate players, let alone cheaters....?
I've given it quite a bit of thought, and I think I'll update it one last time, just to show jagex that they're fools for ruining their flagship enterprise... But it'd be nice to hear other peoples thoughts for or against.

item.title: Consensus on RS2 Cheating
item.dc:creator: @sh_ft sh!ft
item.description:
@sh_ft wrote:

[quote=“speedster239, post:13, topic:165464”][quote author=Ollie link=topic=224505.msg1941718#msg1941718 date=1198183498]
depends if you want lots of little “ankle-biters” adoring you.
personally, i would do it however release bits of code rather then a whole bot, which will be appriciated alot more by the people who can actually put it to some use, rather then getting idiots abusing it.
however thats my thoughts, and i cant make you do something, in the end, its your choice.
[/quote]

To be honest anyone leeching java code in excess isn’t going to get very far. I’m a firm believer in open source code for intelligent collaboration but you should always “give credit where credit is due”. The entire purpose of a community is to gather competent developers so that they can share there knowledge with one another. If your ask for help in an intelligent manner people are going to respect you. But leeching somebody’s code and calling it your own without giving any credit is just wrong.

Anways, I’m still going to continue my work with cheating and look forward to working with Jagex’s next game ;)[/quote]
After reviewing your previous posts all over this forum, I have to say, this is the most mature/intelligent post you have made to date.
